cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on developing a learning architecture for haptic exploration in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of recurrent models of visual attention (RAM) and machine learning methods for feature extraction and control strategy optimization suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the organization of human haptic search behavior, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of online data acquisition and optimization suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
